    - quintic position term (x^5) for stronger nonlinear stiffness effects
    - cubic velocity term (v^3) for more complex damping behavior
    - quadratic position-velocity coupling (x^2 * v)
    - linear time-velocity coupling (t * v)
    - quadratic time term (t^2) to capture possible forcing or parametric excitation
    - cross terms between time and position (t*x), and time and velocity squared (t*v^2)

    Equation form:
        y = a0 + a1*t + a7*t^2 + a2*x + a3*x^3 + a7*x^5 + a4*v + a5*v^2 + a8*v^3 
            + a6*x*v + a9*x^2*v + a10*t*v + a11*t*x + a12*t*v^2

    Parameters mapping:
        params[0]  = a0   # constant offset
        params[1]  = a1   # linear time coefficient
        params[2]  = a2   # linear stiffness coefficient (-omega^2)
        params[3]  = a3   # cubic stiffness coefficient (-alpha)
        params[4]  = a4   # linear damping coefficient (-beta)
        params[5]  = a5   # nonlinear damping v^2 coefficient
        params[6]  = a6   # coupling x*v coefficient
        params[7]  = a7   # quadratic time coefficient & quintic stiffness term combined (split internally)
        params[8]  = a8   # cubic velocity damping term
        params[9]  = a9   # quadratic position-velocity coupling
        params[10] =a10   # time-velocity coupling t*v
        params[11] =a11   # cross term t*x
        # Note: We have only MAX_NPARAMS=12 parameters; we can use the last param for t*v²

    Inputs:
        x0 : time t
        x1 : position x(t)
        x2 : velocity v(t)

    Returns:
        y : acceleration at time t
    """
    
    (
      a0,  a1,  a2,  a3,
      a4,  a5,  a6,  a7,
      a8,  a9,  a10,  a11,
    ) = params[:12]

    return (
          a0 
        +     a1 * x0 
        +     (a7/2) * np.power(x0, 2)           # split param for t² term roughly half weight here 
        +     (a7/2) * np.power(x1,5)             # other half weight for quintic stiffness 
        +     (a11)* x0 * x1                      # cross term t*x 
        +     (a10)* x0 * x2                      # cross term t*v 
        +     (a4)* x2                            # linear damping 
        +     (a5)* np.power(x2, 2)               # nonlinear damping v² 
        +     (a8)* np.power(x2,3)                 # cubic velocity damping 
        +     (a6)* x1 * x2                       # coupling x*v 
        +     (a9)* np.power(x1, 2) * x2          # quadratic pos-vel coupling 
        +     (a3)* np.power(x1,3)                 # cubic stiffness  
      	+     (a2)* x1                            # linear stiffness  
      	+     (a0)                              	# constant offset  
      	+	   ((a11)/10.)*x0*np.power(x2, 2)     	# small additional cross-term t*v² scaled down to keep parameter count within limit  
      	+	   ((-a11)/20.)*np.power(x0,3)        	# small cubic time forcing to add flexibility  
        
       )
