        y = p0 
            + p1 * t 
            + p11 * t^2 
            + (p2 + 0.5 * p1 * t) * x 
            + p4 * x^3 
            + (p3 + 0.3 * p1 * t) * v 
            + p7 * v^2 
            + p10 * v^3 
            + p8 * x*v 
            + p9 * (x^2)*v
            + p5 * sin(omega*t) 
            + p6 * cos(omega*t) 
            + p12_modulated_sin_term
            + p13_modulated_cos_term

    Since we have only 12 parameters total (params[0] to params[11]), we will use:

        params[0] = p0 (constant offset)
        params[1] = p1 (linear in time)
        params[11] = p11 (quadratic in time)
        params[2] = p2 (linear stiffness)
        params[4] = p4 (cubic stiffness)
        params[3] = p3 (linear damping)
        params[7] = p7 (quadratic damping)
        params[10]=p10(cubic damping)
        params[8] = p8 (cross term x*v)
        params[9] = p9 ((x^2)*v cross term)
        params[5] = p5 (sin forcing amplitude)
        params[6] = p6 (cos forcing amplitude)

    Parameters:
    - x0: time array
    - x1: position array at time t
    - x2: velocity array at time t
    - params: array of 12 parameters

    Returns:
