        + a4 * v 
        + a5 * v^2 
        + a9 * v^3
        + a6 * x * v
        + a10 * t * v
        + a11 * t * x
        + (optional) additional cross terms:
            + a12 * x²*v
            + a13 * x*v²
            + a14 * x³*v

    where:
    - t = time (x0)
    - x = position (x1)
    - v = velocity (x2)

    Parameters mapping for extended params array (if extended beyond 12):
        params[0]  = a0   # constant offset
        params[1]  = a1   # linear time coefficient
        params[2]  = a2   # linear stiffness coefficient (-omega²)
        params[3]  = a3   # cubic stiffness coefficient (-alpha)
        params[4]  = a4   # linear damping coefficient (-beta)
        params[5]  = a5   # quadratic velocity damping coefficient
        params[6]  = a6   # coupling term between position and velocity (x*v)
        params[7]  = a7   # quadratic time term (t²)
        params[8]  = a8   # quintic stiffness term (x⁵)
        params[9]  = a9   # cubic velocity damping term (v³)
       params[10]  =a10   # time-velocity coupling term (t*v)
       params[11]  =a11   # time-position coupling term (t*x)
       [params[12]]=a12   # optional: quadratic position times velocity term (x²*v)
       [params[13]]=a13   # optional: position times quadratic velocity term (x*v²)
       [params[14]]=a14   # optional: cubic position times velocity term (x³*v)

    Inputs:
      - x0 : time t
      - x1 : position x(t)
      - x2 : velocity v(t)

    Returns:
      - y : acceleration at time t
    """

    (
      a0,  a1,  a2,  a3,
      a4,  a5,  a6,  a7,
      a8,  a9,  a10,  a11,
    ) = params[:12]

    y = (
          +a0                                  # constant offset
          +a1 * x0                            # linear in time
          +a7 * np.power(x0, 2)              # quadratic in time
          +a2 * x1                           # linear stiffness (-omega²*x)
          +a3 * np.power(x1,3)               # cubic stiffness (-alpha*x³)
          +a8 * np.power(x1,5)               # quintic stiffness for stronger nonlinearity
          +a4 * x2                           # linear damping (-beta*v)
