    """Equation to be evolved.

    Background:
    Calculate Acceleration in Nonl-linear Harmonic Oscillator given Time, Position at time t and Velocity at time t

    Variables:
    - Independents: x0, x1, x2
- Dependent: y

    Parameters:
    - params (np.ndarray): Trainable coefficients used by the equation skeleton.
    """
    """
    Further improved version of the oscillator acceleration equation.

    Terms included:
    - Constant offset
    - Linear time dependence (params[1]*x0)
    - Quadratic time dependence (params[8]*x0**2)
    - Linear position restoring force (params[2]*x1)
    - Cubic position nonlinearity (params[3]*x1**3)
    - Quadratic position term (params[5]*x1**2)
    - Linear velocity damping (params[4]*x2)
    - Quadratic velocity damping/nonlinearity (params[6]*x2**2)
    - Cubic velocity damping/nonlinearity (params[9]*x2**3)  # new term added here
    - Interaction between position and velocity linear terms (params[7]*x1*x2)
    - Higher order mixed nonlinearities:
        * params[10]*(x1**2)*x2
        * params[11]*x1*(x2**2)
    - Sinusoidal forcing in time: params[12] * np.sin(x0)  # extended param index beyond 11
    - Cosine forcing modulated by position: params[13] * np.cos(x0) * x1  # extended param index beyond 11
    
    Note:
        This requires MAX_NPARAMS >= 14.
    
    Parameters:
        x0 : time array
        x1 : position array at time t
        x2 : velocity array at time t
        params : array of parameters with length >=14
    
    Returns:
        y : acceleration array computed from the model.
    
    """
    
    # To avoid index errors if fewer parameters are passed, use conditional defaults:
    
    p = lambda i: params[i] if i < len(params) else 0.0
    
    return (
