    - params (np.ndarray): Trainable coefficients used by the equation skeleton.
    """
    """Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    Adds additional nonlinear and coupling terms while respecting MAX_NPARAMS=12.
    Incorporates parametric excitation term (t * x^2) and quadratic time term (t^2),
    which are physically meaningful for nonlinear oscillators with time-dependent forcing.

    Equation form:
        y = a0 + a1*t + a2*x + a3*x^3 + a4*v + a5*v^2 + a6*x*v 
            + a7*x^5 + a8*v^3 + a9*x^2*v + a10*t*v
            + a11*t*x^2

    Parameters mapping:
        params[0]  = a0   # constant offset
        params[1]  = a1   # linear time coefficient
        params[2]  = a2   # linear stiffness coefficient (-omega^2)
        params[3]  = a3   # cubic stiffness coefficient (-alpha)
        params[4]  = a4   # linear damping coefficient (-beta)
        params[5]  = a5   # nonlinear damping v² coefficient
        params[6]  = a6   # coupling x*v coefficient
        params[7]  = a7   # quintic stiffness coefficient (-gamma)
        params[8]  = a8   # cubic velocity damping term
        params[9]  = a9   # quadratic position-velocity coupling
        params[10] =a10   # time-velocity coupling t*v
        params[11] =a11   # parametric excitation t*x²

