    physical realism of the nonlinear oscillator model:

    - Restoring force terms (linear and cubic in position) are negative (restoring).
    - Damping terms (linear and cubic in velocity) are negative (dissipative).
    - Other nonlinear and cross terms can have flexible signs.

    Model form:
        y = params[0]                         # constant forcing / bias
          + params[1] * x0                    # linear time-dependent forcing
          - abs(params[2]) * x1               # linear restoring force (-k * x)
