    - Linear, quadratic, cubic, and quintic position terms to model complex restoring forces.
    - Linear, quadratic, and cubic velocity terms to capture linear and nonlinear damping.
    - Cross terms between position and velocity of various orders to capture coupling effects.
    - Cross terms involving time with position and velocity to model time-dependent modulation.

